title: Sportivo Trinidense
text:
Sportivo Trinidense, is a Paraguayan <a href="Association%20football">football</a> club based in the <a href="barrio">barrio</a> of <a href="Sant%C3%ADsima%20Trinidad%20%28Asunci%C3%B3n%29">Santísima Trinidad</a>, in <a href="Asunci%C3%B3n">Asunción</a>. The club was founded on 11 August 1935. Their home games are played at the <a href="Estadio%20Mart%C3%ADn%20Torres">Estadio Martín Torres</a>. Their traditional rival is <a href="Club%20Rubio%20%C3%91u">Rubio Ñu</a>, also from barrio Santísima Trinidad. Plays in the <a href="Paraguayan%20Divisi%C3%B3n%20Intermedia">Paraguayan División Intermedia</a> of the Paraguayan league.
History.
The first time the club played in the first division was in 1994.
In 2010 Trinidense returned to the <a href="Paraguayan%20Primera%20Divisi%C3%B3n">Paraguayan First Division</a> after winning the <a href="Paraguayan%20Segunda%20Divisi%C3%B3n">Division Intermedia</a> tournament in 2009.
